---
globs: **/*.vue, **/composables/*.ts, **/utils/*.ts, **/server/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

Built-in auto-imports:
- Vue APIs (`ref`, `computed`, `watch`, lifecycle hooks) and Nuxt composables (`useFetch`, `useRoute`, `useState`, etc.) are auto-imported globally
- Never manually import what Nuxt auto-imports; rely on the auto-import or use `#imports` for explicit imports
- Use `#imports` alias when you need an explicit import for clarity or tooling reasons

Directory auto-imports:
- `app/components/` — Vue components (available in templates without import)
- `app/composables/` — composable functions (available everywhere in app code)
- `app/utils/` — helper functions and utilities (available everywhere in app code)
- `server/utils/` — auto-imported in server context only

Lifecycle context:
- Composables relying on Nuxt context must be called inside `<script setup>`, `setup()`, Nuxt plugins, or route middleware
- Never call Nuxt composables at module top-level outside these contexts: `const config = useRuntimeConfig()` at file root causes errors
- Wrap Nuxt composable calls inside the composable function body: `export const useX = () => { const config = useRuntimeConfig(); ... }`
- In `<script setup>`, composables can be called after `await` (compiler handles context restoration)
